\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 26. P. minuta} Pallas, {\i Reise}{\b  3}: 716 (1776). Like {\b 25} but probably always annual; scapes often shorter than leaves; spikes up to 2 cm; bracts c. 2·5 mm; sepals c. 3 mm; corolla-tube 2·5-3 mm, the lobes 1-1·5 mm, elliptical or ovate-elliptical, acute; stamens usually included; capsule 4-5 mm; seeds 3-3·5 mm. {\i Saline or damp habitats. S.E. Russia, W. Kazakhstan.} Rs (E).
