\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 27. P. loeflingii} L., {\i Sp. Pl. }115 (1753). Annual with one or several rosettes. Leaves 2-7(-10) × 0·1-0·7 cm, linear to linear-lanceolate, entire or remotely dentate, 3-veined, with sparse to dense, patent, rather stiff hairs. Scapes mostly shorter than the leaves, terete, appressed-pubescent; spikes 0·5-2·5 cm, dense. Bracts 2·5-3 mm, wider than long, glabrous. Sepals 1·5-2 mm, equal, almost free, suborbicular, scarious, veined only in lower ¼, glabrous. Corolla-tube c. 1·5 mm, glabrous; lobes c. 1 mm, ovate-lanceolate, subacute. Stamens exserted 0·5-1 mm. Capsule c. 3 mm; seeds 2, 2-2·5 mm, very narrowly cymbiform.{\i  Waste places or sandy ground. C. & S. parts of Iberian peninsula.} Hs Lu.
